<|startoftext|>Dish: the perfect mashed potato
Directions: peel and dice the potato into a similar sized serving size
boil water with salt to cover the entire potato
dice the onion and saute
dice the garlic very finely
place the potato slices in a large saucepan with the onion , garlic , sauteed onion , salt and paprika
add 2 cups of water and bring to a boil
reduce over low heat , partially cover and simmer very gently for an hour
while the liquid is coming to a boil remove the stick of butter and return to the pot
return the potatoes to the pot with the salt & butter
continue to simmer and cover for another hour
when the liquid has come to a good boil add the cream cheese and a little milk
stir the mixture well and remove from the heat
let the cheese cool
mix all the ingredients together in a large mixing bowl
add this to a bowl and then add the butter and salt and pepper to taste
pour the potato mixture on the greased baking sheet
leave to sit for 20-30 minutes
if you like a softer texture like i do , leave for the longer time'<|endoftext|>
