<|startoftext|>Dish: the perfect new york cheesecake
Directions: crust: mix the flour , sugar , and shortening
cut into 2 tablespoons buttermilk with a pastry blender or 2 knives until you have coarse crumbs
do not overbeat
do not add too much buttermilk or you will break the custard
place flour mixture into a large plastic bag and shake to blend well
remove the plastic bag and use for rolling and measuring
remove as much air as possible , add in the remaining buttermilk
seal and squeeze out and replace bag , and divide into 3 equal parts
shape each into a ball , flattening each partially in the middle
roll out each ball into an approximate 1-1 / 2x2-inch circle
pour 2 of the remaining pears into the bottom of a large bowl
dredge each round in the egg and then the nut mixture in pears
toss half of the pears in the reserved pured egg and dot a small amount of the custard over the pears , leaving the remaining pears in the middle
bake in a 400f oven for 8-10 minutes or until the bottom of the pears are slightly crisp
top with 2 or 3 of the sliced pear halves , then top with remaining pears
garnish with the remaining pears
serve cheesecakes in the bowl with the sourcream
to make the sourcream: combine the sour cream , milk and chocolate extract , stirring well
transfer to a blender and process until smooth
toss with the prepared sour
